 A traffic officer killed his girlfriend before turning the gun on himself on Sunday evening. Securicon Reaction officers and task team members, as well as EMS, responded to reports of alleged shots fired in the rented flat on a private residence in Zebra Street on Sunday night at 20:23. ALSO READ: Taxi hits and kills giraffe, which then falls onto another tourist vehicle The door had to be broken open for them to gain access. The bodies of the man and woman, both in their late 30s, were discovered inside. Both were declared dead on the scene by Securicon paramedics. The scene was secured and handed over to SAPS Komatipoort detectives. The deceased are believed to have been in a long-term relationship. Their names have been withheld until their next of kin have been notified. ALSO READ: Threat of drought looms over Barberton